President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Pennsylvania due to a severe winter storm that began on February 4, 2014. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. The declaration specifically applies to the counties of Bucks, Chester, Delaware, Lancaster, Montgomery, Philadelphia, and York. FEMA is authorized to identify and provide necessary equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent federal funding, and Donald L. Keldsen has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.